Install conveyors accurately from the blueprints and/or schematics; 
Diagnose and repair conveyor problems as needed; 
Perform conveyor maintenance as required; 
Provide technical support to customers and other technicians; 
Adhere to safety standards and ensure a safe work area; 
Perform housekeeping and general clean up duties; 
QUALIFICATIONS /  REQUIREMENTS 
Must be eligible to work in the United States;
 Must have a High School diploma or GED equivalent; 
Must pass Weld Test; 
Must have own tools (required tool list will be provided);
 Required to complete the OSHA 10-Hour training course unless hold a current, valid OSHA 10 card from an OSHA authorized trainer; 
Must adhere to site rules and take any additional required site-specific training to ensure compliance;
 3+ years Millwright experience required with a preference for at least 2 years of conveyor installation, steel fabrication or welding experience; 
Excellent mechanical aptitude along with welding and fabrication skills; 
Ability to read and interpret blueprints, schematics and detailed drawings related to conveyor equipment and related machinery;
 Basic electrical knowledge; 
Ability to understand and follow verbal and written instructions; 
Good interpersonal and customer service skills; 
Ability to work flexible hours and to work independently; 
Ability to work 40-60 hours per week or more, if needed; 
Must be willing and able to travel frequently and to perform work at worksites at locations throughout the United States for extended periods of time in order to complete projects; 
Attendance and punctuality on site are an essential job function.

